Summary & Conclusion¶

In this experimentation, 'used car price dataset' is used. (https://www.kaggle.com/kukuroo3/used-car-price-dataset-competition-format) \ At the beginning an initial linear regression model is created to predict the score attribute. For categorical variables, one-hot encoding and for the numerical variables standart scaling is applied as preprocessing. (See section 1)

In the second part, after plotting each variable against target and inspecting them, several scores are created (see sections 2.1 and 2.2) \ After experimenting with a couple of different variations, it is seen score development increased model performance only by small percentage.

As it can be seen in the table below, with score development the MAPE score increased by ~1,5%.

r2 MAE MSE RMSE MAPE
After score development (Test) 0.9034 3205.06 2.66219e+07 5159.64 0.429
Original Model (Test) 0.8971 3341.98 2.83519e+07 5324.65 0.443

def plot_variables_against_target(data, target_col_name, categorical_features=[], numerical_features=[], ncols=3, fig_with_per_col=12, fig_hight_per_row=10):
    columns = categorical_features + numerical_features
    print(f"Number of features: {len(columns)}")
    nrows = math.ceil(len(columns)/ncols)
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(ncols=ncols, nrows=nrows, figsize=(fig_with_per_col*ncols, fig_hight_per_row*nrows))
    fig.subplots_adjust(hspace=0.5)
    
    axes = (ax for ax in axes.flat)
    
    for col in categorical_features:
        ax_ = sns.boxplot(data=data, x=col, y=target_col_name, 
                    order=data.groupby(col)[target_col_name].median().sort_values().index.tolist(),
                    ax=next(axes), orient='v',
                   )
        ax_.set_title(col)
        
        if data[col].nunique() >10:
            ax_.set_xticklabels(ax_.get_xticklabels(),rotation=90)
        
    for col in numerical_features:
        sns.regplot(data=data, x=col, y=target_col_name, line_kws={'color': 'g'}, ax=next(axes))
        
    plt.show()

numerical_features=['mileage', 'tax', 'mpg','engineSize']
categorical_features=['brand', 'model', 'year', 'transmission', 'fuelType' ]
target_col_name='price'

x_train = pd.read_csv('X_train.csv')
y_train = pd.read_csv('y_train.csv')
train_data = x_train.merge(y_train, on='carID', how='inner')

x_train = train_data[numerical_features+categorical_features]

x_test = pd.read_csv('X_test.csv')
y_test = pd.read_csv('y_test.csv')
test_data = x_test.merge(y_test, on='carID', how='inner')

x_test = test_data[numerical_features+categorical_features]
y_test = test_data[target_col_name]

def regression_results(y_true, y_pred, group=""):
    r2=metrics.r2_score(y_true, y_pred)
    mean_absolute_error=metrics.mean_absolute_error(y_true, y_pred) 
    mse=metrics.mean_squared_error(y_true, y_pred) 
    median_absolute_error=metrics.median_absolute_error(y_true, y_pred)
    mape = np.abs((y_true - y_pred) / y_true).mean(axis=0)
    

    return pd.DataFrame.from_records([[round(r2,4), round(mean_absolute_error,4), round(mse,4), round(np.sqrt(mse),4), round(np.sqrt(mape),4)]],
                                     
                                     index=[group], 
                                     columns=['r2', 'MAE', 'MSE', 'RMSE', 'MAPE'])

numerical_transformer = Pipeline(
    steps=[("scaler", StandardScaler())]
)


categorical_transformer = OneHotEncoder(handle_unknown="ignore")

preprocessor = ColumnTransformer(
    transformers=[
        ("num", numerical_transformer, numerical_features),
        ("cat", categorical_transformer, categorical_features),
    ]
)


reg = Pipeline(
    steps=[("preprocessor", preprocessor), ("classifier", LinearRegression())]
)



reg.fit(x_train, y_train)

original_model_result = pd.concat([regression_results(y_true=y_val, y_pred=reg.predict(x_val), group="Validation"),
                                       regression_results(y_true=y_test, y_pred=reg.predict(x_test), group="Test")])

2.2 Feature Engineering: Score creation¶

Brand Variable:

  • We can define merc, bmw, audi as luxury segment, ford, toyota, vw as mid segment and hyundi, vauxhall, skoda as low segment we can derive a segment score 3,2 and 1 correspondingly.
  • We can derive a production year score based on year variable. 
      - 2018-2020: New (3)
  - 2015-2017 : Mid (2)
  - pre 2015: Old (1)

  • Similarly we can derive mileage_score based on milage varibla

      - 0-25000: (3)
  - 25000-50000: (2)
  - >50000: 1

  • Finally by multiplying handcrafted scores, we can calculate a price score.

In [28]:
def score_developmet(x_train, x_val, x_test, y_train, y_val, y_test, drop_original_features=False, calculate_final_score=True):
    x_train_mod, x_val_mod, x_test_mod, y_train_mod, y_val_mod, y_test_mod = x_train.copy(), x_val.copy(), x_test.copy(), y_train.copy(), y_val.copy(), y_test.copy()
    
    #brand_segment_score
    x_train_mod['brand_segment_score'] = x_train_mod.brand.replace(['merc', 'bmw', 'audi'], 3).replace(['merc', 'bmw', 'audi'], 3).replace(['ford', 'toyota', 'vw'], 2).replace(['hyundi', 'vauxhall', 'skoda'], 1)
    x_val_mod['brand_segment_score'] = x_val_mod.brand.replace(['merc', 'bmw', 'audi'], 3).replace(['merc', 'bmw', 'audi'], 3).replace(['ford', 'toyota', 'vw'], 2).replace(['hyundi', 'vauxhall', 'skoda'], 1)
    x_test_mod['brand_segment_score'] = x_test_mod.brand.replace(['merc', 'bmw', 'audi'], 3).replace(['merc', 'bmw', 'audi'], 3).replace(['ford', 'toyota', 'vw'], 2).replace(['hyundi', 'vauxhall', 'skoda'], 1)
    
    #year_score
    year_score = lambda x: 3 if x >=4 else 2 if x>=2 else 1
    x_train_mod['year_score'] = x_train_mod.year.apply(year_score)
    x_val_mod['year_score'] = x_val_mod.year.apply(year_score)
    x_test_mod['year_score'] = x_test_mod.year.apply(year_score)
    
    
    
    #mileage_score
    mileage_score = lambda x: 3 if x <=25000 else 2 if x<=50000 else 1
    x_train_mod['mileage_score'] = x_train_mod.mileage.apply(mileage_score)
    x_val_mod['mileage_score'] = x_val_mod.mileage.apply(mileage_score)
    x_test_mod['mileage_score'] = x_test_mod.mileage.apply(mileage_score)
    
    
    # Final Score
    if calculate_final_score:
        price_score = lambda row: (row.brand_segment_score * row.brand_segment_score * row.mileage_score)
        x_train_mod['price_score'] = x_train_mod.apply(price_score, axis=1)
        x_val_mod['price_score'] = x_val_mod.apply(price_score, axis=1)
        x_test_mod['price_score'] = x_test_mod.apply(price_score, axis=1)
    
    if drop_original_features:
        x_train_mod.drop(['brand', 'year', 'mileage'], inplace=True, axis=1)
        x_val_mod.drop(['brand', 'year', 'mileage'], inplace=True, axis=1)
        x_test_mod.drop(['brand', 'year', 'mileage'], inplace=True, axis=1)
    
    return x_train_mod, x_val_mod, x_test_mod, y_train_mod, y_val_mod, y_test_mod

                                                                                           drop_original_features=False, calculate_final_score=True)

scoring_features = list(set(['brand_segment_score','year_score','mileage_score', 'price_score']).intersection(set(x_train_mod.columns.tolist())))
numerical_features_mod= list(set(numerical_features+scoring_features).intersection(set(x_train_mod.columns.tolist())))
categorical_features_mod=list(set(categorical_features).intersection(set(x_train_mod.columns.tolist())))
